  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowerment of Mothers of Vulnerable Girls in Waterloo, Sierra Leone</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will use the Nelson Family Foundation (NFF) grant to support mothers of vulnerable girls in rural areas in Sierra Leone, to set up business cooperatives (co -ops). The women will be taught group dynamics,train how to drive tricycle, receive training on food preparation, good hygiene and healthy eating practices. On completion of their training, they will be supplied with a start -up grant and 2 solar powered kehkehs which they will use to sell food &amp; drinks within their communities. Their mobile kitchens will move to lucrative selling locations from day to day. When the mobile units are not being used to transport and sell cooked food, they will be used as commercial transport for market items or agricultural produce for other women in the community, as well as opportunities for providing transportation services.</narrative>
  </description>
